			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Look at it this way-while these people are making their living in the bazaar, they arent in your camps</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A lot of people 2 box, and have a bazaar toon up on the 2nd account 24/7.
<br />
They are still at your camp, and yes, in some cases are underselling you or overselling to make money. The shared bank slot allows them easy transfer and people can litterly farm, undersell or oversell to the point of non stop til their new price becomes the accepted standard.
<br />

<br />
Though I can see your point the bazaar really has made it much more complicated as to whether its worthy of a rant for overselling or underselling, depending on the item being sold.
<br />

<br />
A case in point;
<br />

<br />
during my growing years, when i hit 56. it was apparant i needed to make some real money for upgrades before i could ever dream of going to 65. 
<br />

<br />
I chose AC as my farming zone. Mostly empty, a decided lack of mob information on the web, especially the castle, with soloable named mobs on either side of the castle.
<br />

<br />
All you had to do was find them.
<br />

<br />
Never being able to get reliable mob info on the web I found them the hard way, especially the castle named mobs. By crawling, exploring, dying often (with no rez available) over the course of weeks. I stopped at 60 for 100AAs, and farmed all named outside the castle.
<br />

<br />
took a lot longer to locate castle mobs. the exit and so on.
<br />

<br />
In comes mr. mage. I show him a couple camps. Being a mage the two camps i showed him was the Primalist and the bloodmage as those are 2 nice caster items.
<br />

<br />
The robe at this time sold for 7-8k and the mask 12-15k
<br />

<br />
Mr. Mage sat and farmed both for weeks, underselling all in bazaar with  his 2nd account bazaar toon to the point robes were going for 3k and masks 6k. 
<br />

<br />
He lived at both camps.
<br />

<br />
Needless to say I showed him no other camps. I had spent far too much time and deaths to have the weapons and armor of the Bloodpriest, warlord and others undercut to the point my efforts were fruitless.
<br />

<br />
This mage never explored or looked or took a risk o find other camps. He never entered the castle, even at 65, and pray tell that's how it should be.
<br />

<br />
His underselling is deserving of a rant, not overselling. At one time grimling masks sold for 30k afterall, and at 12k they are a bargain. 
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, I waited weeks for Sha's revenge as I was not about to pay 100k for this, the price a couple people were asking.
<br />

<br />
The spell is so rare, and I've yet won a rune roll, but come'on, 100k?
<br />

<br />
Finally had someone put one up for 50k, which in itself is high, but i had 50k, and frankly have nothing at all to buy now from bazaar that would be an upgrade to what I have.....probably buy a horse just to have something to spend money on.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
