				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I never understood why people get angry at the pricing in the bazaar.  
<br />

<br />
If you dont like the price dont buy it.  
<br />

<br />
If someone sells his item lower than you simply let him sell his right away and then sell yours at your price later.  
<br />

<br />
Someone buys your item and then sells it at a higher price?  Be happy you sold your item and then go spend your plat you just made.
<br />

<br />
For some people the best part of EQ is the buying and selling game that goes on in EQ.  My bestfriends girlfriend only stays in the bazaar doing this.  She makes tons of plat for him and she thinks its great fun.  
<br />

<br />
Its part of the EQ economy that all items will fall in prices that simply cannot be changed.  I have never been a fan of farmers but if your item you been farming for weeks suddenly sells for only half the price it did you have to look at yourself first and realize cannot keep flooding the market with the same item and expect the price to stay the same.  
<br />

<br />
Not trying to insult or flame anyone but its just simple economics</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
