				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You can always pricefix your own stuff if you have more than one account, and multiples of the same object.  It's a rather simple way to rip off peeps who live in the bazaar.
<br />

<br />
Say you have 2 copies of a spell that normally sells for 2K and you want to offload one fast but still make a proffit.  Go into the bazaar while nobody is selling those spells.  On one trader price the spell for 10-12K.  On the main trader price the spell for 5-6K and announce OOC that you are underselling the competition by as much as 5K.  Usually you well sell the item in a matter of minutes if the right bazaar living people are not AFK.  And you just over sold an item by 3K.  This works quite well at least on the rathe.  I've made over 100K selling common drops this way.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=696935" target="_blank" class="postlink">Oomi</a>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://eq.frayedknot.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Frayed Knot - The Rathe</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
