			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have to agree that the bazaar is a good part of the game. Some people prefer the bazaar for their playing experience. It's sure helped me. I'm a person that buys low and sells high, but I'm also the consumate lowby who's never had more than 1.5 k on hand at a time, so I probably didn't hurt too many people. My problem with buying low and selling high is that I never have enough cash to make it really pay off, or some of the deals I find I actually need so I can't resell them just yet. My biggest score was finding a spell called Sun Storm on a vendor for a little over 5 pp and selling it for 400 pp (a true lowby like I said). I maybe could have made more, but like the one fella said, some times I sell low and it helps others out, sometimes I buy low and sell high, which helps the seller get rid of what they obviously are trying to dump quickly, and helps me by giving me a cheap item I can use or resell and hopefully helps the resold buyer get an item they want bad enough to pay the price I put on it. It's all good. If you want the deal, then spend more time in the bazaar.
<br />

<br />
As far as campers go, that's a different discussion. I know that I like more items in game. Lower prices is a good thing for the majority although it kills the few that are farming. The way I see it, the farmer does not deserve to have a happier life at the expense of everyone else's wallet, so your preaching a sermon I disagree with when you try to make me feel sorry for your loss of profit when farming.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
