			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There's an interesting situation on Innoruuk server right now, ever since the last patch.
<br />

<br />
Velium, which used to sell at 20 plat per small piece, is now selling at 500 plat (it is actually _selling_ at 500, I've had some people buy it from me at that price) since every aspiring smith on the server needs it to get to 222, and even 1k per combine is cheaper than all their other routes.
<br />

<br />
Whereas Coldain Velium Temper is selling at about 10 plat each. Seems after the patch, a dwarf in Thurgadin was giving the stuff away, so entire guilds have outfitted all their twinks with backpacks and banks full of the stuff. Rather amusing when you see a group of level 1 bazaar twinks selling 1600 CVT each (and nothing else) all competing on who can get the lowest price for their (stolen) wares.
<br />

<br />
So anyway... that just goes to illustrate how supply and demand have powerful influences on the EQ economy. It's not personal greed.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=351048"><img src="http://www.foxyonline.com/prrsig.jpg" border="0" width="450" height="180" alt="Click to view Magelo"></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
